                td 3 Eggs  |   100g

        .c-step-cook-list
          .c-step-cook-list__item
            .c-step-egg
              span.small Step
              span.number 1
            .c-step-detail Preheat oven to 400ºF.
          .c-step-cook-list__item
            .c-step-egg
              span.small Step
              span.number 2
            .c-step-detail Preheat Combine dry ingredients and pulse in food processor. Add in butter cubes and pulse until coarse meal forms.
          .c-step-cook-list__item
            .c-step-egg
              span.small Step
              span.number 3
            .c-step-detail
              |Add to wet ingredients and fold, being careful not to overwork dough. <br>
              |Roll out dough to 1” thickness and cut dough in half. Take one half of dough and stack it on top of the other half for tall flaky layers.
          .c-step-cook-list__item
            .c-step-egg
              span.small Step
              span.number 4
            .c-step-detail
              |Roll dough out again to 1” and cut out 10 biscuits with 3” circular dough cutter. Alternatively, cut squares for additional yield.
          .c-step-cook-list__item
            .c-step-egg
              span.small Step
              span.number 5
            .c-step-detail Place biscuits on half sheet tray lined with parchment paper.
          .c-step-cook-list__item
            .c-step-egg
              span.small Step
              span.number 6
            .c-step-detail Chill in freezer for 10 minutes, remove, and bake for 10-12 minutes, or until done.

